Florence Police seek help to identify several people
FLORENCE, S.C. -- Investigators are asking for the publicâ€™s assistance to identify several people wanted for questioning.
The people are wanted for questioning in connection with a shoplifting incident at the South Irby Street Walmart on Feb. 12, according to a release issued by the Florence Police Department.
Anyone with information is asked to contact the Florence Police Department at 843-665-3191 or Crime Stoppers (1-888-CRIMESC / 1-888-274-6372).
